<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,224,676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,334,302,328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Etymology</emphasis>
: derived from the Egyptian 
<taxonomicName box="[675,756,303,328]" class="Reptilia" family="Reptilia" genus="Uraeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Reptilia" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[675,756,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">uraeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a symbol of the goddess Wadjet in the shape of a cobra with a spread hood, which formed part of the head-dress of Egyptian divinities and kings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
